F|Palazzo Medici Façade Codes|Rusticated stone exterior @ Palazzo Medici Riccardi -> architectural symbol of Medici power. Cosimo il Vecchio rejected Brunelleschi's "too regal" design [1] -> chose Michelozzo 1444. Style signaling humility without overt princely display.|Palazzo Medici Riccardi @ Via Cavour 3 -> rusticated base / smooth upper stories still legible today.|H
P|Cappella dei Magi Propaganda|Benozzo Gozzoli frescoes 1459 -> Magi procession = Medici family portraits disguised as biblical narrative [2]. Lorenzo il Magnifico as Magus -> divine legitimacy claim. Medici family commissioned frescoes.|Cappella dei Magi @ Palazzo Medici Riccardi -> Gozzoli fresco north/east walls.|H
F|Orsanmichele Guild Statues|Orsanmichele @ Via dell'Arte della Lana -> exterior niches assigned to guilds by city decree 1339. Guilds competed commissioning bronze statues [3] -> statues of patron saints. Competitive display of guild wealth and prestige.|Niche facades @ Orsanmichele -> Ghiberti's St. John Baptist (Calimala) / Donatello's St. Mark (Linaioli) still in situ or cast replicas.|H
S|Piazza della Signoria Executions|Piazza della Signoria -> site of Savonarola execution 1498 [5] AND Pazzi conspirators hanged 1478 post-failed assassination. Round marble plaque marks Savonarola's pyre. Public executions used to reinforce control after political crises.|Round marble plaque @ Piazza della Signoria pavement -> exact execution site marked permanently.|H
F|Spedale degli Innocenti Branding|Spedale degli Innocenti 1419 -> Brunelleschi loggia commissioned by Arte della Seta [6]. First orphanage in Europe. Della Robbia terracotta roundels represent "putti" (innocents). Foundling wheel site marked by window and plaque.|Spedale degli Innocenti @ Piazza SS. Annunziata -> loggia roundels / foundling wheel site marked in situ.|H
C|Laurentian Library Access Control|Biblioteca Medicea Laurenziana -> Michelangelo vestibule 1524 commissioned by Clement VII (Giulio de' Medici) [7]. Library holds Greek manuscripts collected during Ottoman crisis. Staircase design ("scala impossibile") challenges architectural norms.|Biblioteca Medicea Laurenziana @ Piazza San Lorenzo -> Michelangelo vestibule / reading room accessible.|H